Window Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_IDCMP: ( ti_Tag=$8000006A )

Specify which IDCMP events your window
requires in ti_Data. (OR them together).
(See the IDCMP Page for more details).


Window Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_Flags: ( ti_Tag=$8000006B )

Multiple initialisation of the window Flags
equivalent to NewWindow.Flags. The required
WFLG_ constants are OR'ed to give ti_Data.


Window Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_Gadgets: ( ti_Tag=$8000006C )

Specify a pointer to the first in the
linked list of Gadget structures to be included
in this window, in ti_Data.


Window Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_Checkmark: ( ti_Tag=$8000006D )

Specify a pointer to an Image structure
which is to be used as the ckeckmark image
in this window's menus.


Window Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_Title: ( ti_Tag=$8000006E )

Specify the default window title as a
pointer to a null terminated string
in ti_Data.


Window Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_ScreenTitle: ( ti_Tag=$8000006F )

Specify the screen title to be displayed
whilst the window is active, as a pointer 
to a null terminated string in ti_Data.


