WA_InnerWidth: ( ti_Tag=$80000076 )

Specify the dimensions region inside the
border, independed of the border widths
in ti_Data.
When using WA_InnerWidth and WA_InnerHeight,
probably want WA_AutoAdjust set also.


Window  Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_InnerHeight: ( ti_Tag=$80000077 )

Specify the dimensions region inside the
border, independed of the border widths
in ti_Data.
When using WA_InnerWidth and WA_InnerHeight,
probably want WA_AutoAdjust set also.


Window Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_PubScreenFallBack: ( ti_Tag=$80000078 )

ti_Data is a boolean specifying whether a
visitor window should "fall back" to the
default public screen if the named public
screen is not available.
(Only useful when used with WA_PubScreenName)


Window Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_PubScreen: ( ti_Tag=$80000079 )

Specify to open the window as a visitor
window on the public screen whose address
is in ti_Data.


Window Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_PubScreenName: ( ti_Tag=$8000007A )

Specify to open the window as a visitor
window on the public screen whose name is
given by a pointer to a null terminated 
string in ti_Data.


Window Attribute Tags
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_CustomScreen: ( ti_Tag=$8000007A )

Specify a pointer to the Screen structure
of a screen created by this application,
on which the window is to be opened.

